<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-4622] KafkaConsumer does not properly handle authorization errors from offset fetches</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4622</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s possible to receive both group and topic authorization exceptions from an OffsetFetch, but the consumer currently treats this as generic unexpected errors. We should probably return &lt;tt&gt;GroupAuthorizationException&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;TopicAuthorizationException&lt;/tt&gt; to be consistent with the other consumer APIs. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13034054">KAFKA-4622</key>
